    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Your task consists of analyzing texts.\n\ninput: {{ $json.secties.Functieschaal }}\nor\n{{ $json.secties.vereisten }}\nor {{ $json.formatted_text_voor_ai }} and {{ $json.secties.gunningscriteria }} (only use these if no hourly rate or salary scale can be found in the first two)\n\nIf a maximum hourly amount is mentioned, output this amount as 'gain' and proceed to step 2!\n\nIf only a scale is given, look at the scale number and assign an amount according to the following criteria:\n\nScale 8 -> 80\n\nScale 9 -> 90\n\nScale 10 -> 105\n\nScale 11 -> 115\n\nScale 12 -> 135\n\nScale 13 -> 148\n\nScale 14 -> 160\nand output this as 'gain'.\n\nIf you cannot find a maximum hourly wage anywhere, or no scale is specified, then 'gain' is equal to 9999. But only and exclusively in the case that no maximum hourly wage or scale is found.\n\nExtract from {{ $json.secties.Fee_Flextender }} how many euros of fee are requested per hour and output this as 'fee'.\n\nIf a comma is used in a number, change it to a period (example: 12,34 becomes 12.34).\n\nNOTE: If there is a maximum hourly rate that is lower than the scale indication, use the maximum hourly rate. The scale is an indication; the maximum is binding.\n\nOutput exclusively the raw JSON. Start directly with { and end with }. Do not use markdown formatting (so no ```json), no explanatory text, and no wrapping objects.\n\n{\n\"hourly\": 12345,\n\"fee\": 12.34\n}",
